# Polaris Web Components (App Home)

## FormData — NEVER use native form submission

`s-text-field`, `s-email-field`, `s-number-field`, `s-text-area` are NOT form-associated.
`new FormData(form)` collects zero values. Always harvest manually:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
const get = (name: string) =>
  (form.querySelector(`[name="${name}"]`) as HTMLElement & { value: string })?.value ?? "";
const fd = new FormData();
fd.append("name", get("name"));
submit(fd, { method: "post" });

// ❌ WRONG — sends empty strings
submit(form);
// ❌ WRONG — does not trigger React Router
form.requestSubmit();
```

## s-section slots — App Home only has `children`

App Home `s-section` has NO `primary-action` or `secondary-actions` slots.
Those slots only exist in Customer Account / POS extensions.
Put buttons inside the section body using a flex div instead:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<s-section heading="Product catalog">
  <div style={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "flex-end" }}>
    <s-button variant="primary" onClick={handleSync}>Sync</s-button>
  </div>
</s-section>

// ❌ WRONG — button is silently dropped
<s-section heading="Product catalog">
  <s-button slot="primary-action">Sync</s-button>
</s-section>
```

## Valid prop values (common mistakes)

| Component | ❌ Invalid | ✅ Valid |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `s-banner` | `tone="caution"` | `tone="warning"` |
| `s-text` | `tone="subdued"` | no tone prop; use `style` |
| `s-stack` | `align="center"` | no align prop; use flex div |
| `s-button` | `size="slim"` | use `variant` only |
| `s-button` | `icon="refresh"` string variant | pass icon name; variant is separate |

## Icon buttons

```tsx
<s-button icon="refresh" variant="primary" onClick={handleSync}>
  Sync products
</s-button>
```
